# Optional: enables the "Google Map" tab in the local viewer.
#
# When both vars below are set, viewer/trip.html shows an extra "Google Map"
# tab (alongside the default MapLibre+OpenStreetMap "Map" tab). Without them,
# the tab stays hidden and everything else works as usual.
#
# How to use:
#   1. Copy this file:  cp .env.local.example .env.local
#   2. Fill in the values from your Google Cloud Console (links below).
#   3. Restart `python3 -m http.server` and reload viewer/trip.html.
#
# How the viewer reads it:
#   The viewer is a static page (no build step), so there's no `process.env`.
#   `viewer/lib/env-config.js` fetches `.env.local` from the repo root via
#   HTTP and parses `KEY=value` lines client-side. This works because
#   `python3 -m http.server` serves any file in the directory — including
#   `.env.local`. Don't expose this server beyond localhost.
#
# Security:
#   Both values land in your browser at runtime, so a hostile party with
#   network access to your local server could read them. For tighter control,
#   restrict the API key in Google Cloud Console:
#     - Application restrictions → HTTP referrers → http://localhost:8000/*
#     - API restrictions → enable only "Maps JavaScript API"
#
# Get the API key:
#   https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis/credentials
#
# Get the Map ID (for vector + custom styling):
#   https://console.cloud.google.com/google/maps-apis/studio/maps

GOOGLE_MAPS_API_KEY=
GOOGLE_MAP_ID=
